<hw>pelecypod</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A marine or freshwater
mollusk having a soft body with platelike gills enclosed within two
shells hinged together; a member of the Pelecypoda.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bivalve, lamellibranch.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

